  <main id="main"><header class="page-hero page-hero--diagonal"><div class="container"><div class="breadcrumbs"><a href="index.html">Home</a> / <a href="missions.html">Missions</a> / National Capacity</div><span class="kicker">Humanity-scale mission</span><h1>National Capacity & Resilience</h1><p>Building strength in infrastructure, cybersecurity, emergency preparedness, public systems, science, technology, and institutional readiness.</p></div></header><nav class="anchor-nav anchor-nav--index" aria-label="On this page"><div class="container"><a href="#focus"><span>01</span>Areas of focus</a><a href="#process"><span>02</span>How it works</a><a href="#overview"><span>03</span>Overview</a><a href="#principles"><span>04</span>Principles</a><a href="#next"><span>05</span>Next steps</a></div></nav><section class="section section--mist" id="focus"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">The field of action</span><h2>Where this mission concentrates disciplined effort</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>National capacity is the accumulated ability of institutions, infrastructure, people, knowledge, and networks to meet essential needs and adapt under pressure.</p></div><div class="focus-bento"><article class="dimension-card"><span>01</span><LegacyIcon name="compass" /><h3>Critical infrastructure</h3><p>Support reliable physical, digital, logistical, energy, water, and communications systems.</p></article><article class="dimension-card"><span>02</span><LegacyIcon name="institution" /><h3>Preparedness and continuity</h3><p>Improve risk analysis, scenario planning, exercises, coordination, recovery, and institutional learning.</p></article><article class="dimension-card"><span>03</span><LegacyIcon name="lightbulb-o" /><h3>Cyber and digital resilience</h3><p>Protect essential services, strengthen security practice, and design technology for dependable public use.</p></article><article class="dimension-card"><span>04</span><LegacyIcon name="handshake-o" /><h3>Knowledge and workforce</h3><p>Build scientific, technical, operational, and leadership capability for long-term readiness.</p></article></div></div></section><section class="section" id="process"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">From intent to practice</span><h2>From a large mission to useful work</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Humanity-scale language must lead to specific contribution. Each appointment narrows a broad challenge into work a Fellow and host can pursue responsibly.</p></div><div class="process-stair"><article class="step"><h3>Understand the field</h3><p>Map the challenge, affected communities, existing efforts, evidence, and important constraints. Here, attend to critical infrastructure: Support reliable physical, digital, logistical, energy, water, and communications systems.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>Locate leverage</h3><p>Identify a bounded question or institutional need where the Fellow&#x27;s capabilities can matter. Here, attend to preparedness and continuity: Improve risk analysis, scenario planning, exercises, coordination, recovery, and institutional learning.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>Contribute with discipline</h3><p>Work through a trusted host, respect domain knowledge, and produce useful, reviewable outputs. Here, attend to cyber and digital resilience: Protect essential services, strengthen security practice, and design technology for dependable public use.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>Strengthen what endures</h3><p>Share learning and reinforce the relationships, knowledge, and systems that carry the mission forward. Here, attend to knowledge and workforce: Build scientific, technical, operational, and leadership capability for long-term readiness.</p></article></div></div></section><section class="section thesis-opening" id="overview"><div class="container"><span class="thesis-index" aria-hidden="true">01</span><div class="prose"><span class="eyebrow">A humanity-scale mission</span><h2>Systems prepared to carry public responsibility</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>National capacity is the accumulated ability of institutions, infrastructure, people, knowledge, and networks to meet essential needs and adapt under pressure.</p><p>Resilience is not only emergency response. It includes maintenance, foresight, workforce, coordination, learning, and trustworthy systems before a crisis arrives.</p><p>Critical infrastructure establishes the point of entry; knowledge and workforce defines what should remain after the immediate work is complete.</p></div><blockquote>Critical infrastructure establishes the point of entry; knowledge and workforce defines what should remain after the immediate work is complete.</blockquote></div></section><section class="section" id="principles"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">Mission guardrails</span><h2>How ambitious work remains responsible</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Scale increases the need for context, collaboration, and durable public value.</p></div><div class="principle-pillars"><article class="card card--numbered"><span class="card__number">01</span><h3>Listen before acting</h3><p>Understand existing knowledge, lived experience, and institutional context before defining a response. In this context, consider critical infrastructure.</p></article><article class="card card--numbered"><span class="card__number">02</span><h3>Work across boundaries</h3><p>Bring disciplines and sectors together when no single profession can address the whole challenge. In this context, consider preparedness and continuity.</p></article><article class="card card--numbered"><span class="card__number">03</span><h3>Build durable capacity</h3><p>Favor work that strengthens people, knowledge, and systems beyond the immediate intervention. In this context, consider cyber and digital resilience.</p></article></div></div></section><section class="section close-ledger" id="next"><div class="container"><span class="close-ledger__index" aria-hidden="true">05</span><div><div><h2>Translate a large mission into useful work</h2><p>Begin with critical infrastructure, then define a contribution your capabilities or institution can support.</p></div><div class="actions"><a class="button button--gold" href="apply.html">Express interest</a><a class="button button--outline" href="missions.html">Explore all missions</a></div></div><aside class="related-panel"><span class="eyebrow">Continue exploring</span><h3>Related pathways</h3><ul class="related-list"><li><a href="missions.html">All missions</a></li><li><a href="mission-fellowships.html">Mission Fellowships</a></li><li><a href="fellowship-programs.html">Fellowship programs</a></li></ul></aside></div></section></main>

